UML:TaggedValue.value: This package to contain explanation of the nature of the HollowWorld modelling template
Guidance and specifications on how to embed documentation content within the UML model.
Guidance and specifications on how to embed documentation content within the UML model.

Adding documentation to your model is easy. Every "element" in your model (e.g. all classes, attributes, associations) should have some textual documentation in the "notes" field of the model. (See documentation at https://www.seegrid.csiro.au/twiki/bin/view/AppSchemas/ModelDocumentation for more information and screen shots of where the notes should be created for the different model element types).
The tool used to auto-generate documentation from the model expects to find notes in only these places. You need not have comments for every model element but it is good practice to do so and it gives the auto-generated documentation a much more usable and complete appearance.

The GASDoc tool (see https://www.seegrid.csiro.au/twiki/bin/view/AppSchemas/ModelDocumentation) is a tool for generating API documentation for GML Application Schema (GAS) models.
It is similar to API documentation tools that exist for modern programming languages (like Javadoc for Java). It takes an input in the form of an XML document and generates a set of linked HTML pages as output. The input is an XMI (XML Metadata Interchange) representation of a GML Application Schema UML model.

See
https://www.seegrid.csiro.au/twiki/bin/view/AppSchemas/ModelDocumentation
for more information on the model documentation and generation process.
